Class SvrStringLocaleAwareComparator

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DomainComparator, DomainPlugIn, PlugIn, java.io.Serializable, java.util.Comparator<java.lang.Object>

    public class SvrStringLocaleAwareComparator
extends AbstractComparator
    A locale-aware comparator for the SVR_STRING and SVR_UNBOUNDED_STRING domains. There is no distinction between these domains for comparisons. This comparator uses the sorting rules defined for the active locale to compare strings. The sorting rules used are those defined by Java's java.text.Collator class.

    • Method Detail

      • compare

        public int compare(java.lang.Object string1,
                   java.lang.Object string2)
        Compares two objects that must be strings. The comparison applies the sorting rules of the language indicated by the active locale.
        Parameters:
        string1 - The first string to be compared.
        string2 - The second string to be compared.
        Returns:
        The result of the locale-aware comparison.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if either string is null.
        java.lang.ClassCastException - if either object is not a java.lang.String.
        See Also:
        Comparator.compare(java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object)
